    pearls: ["The MOST IMPORTANT intervention in TEN is IMMEDIATE discontinuation of the causative drug — every day of delay increases mortality by an estimated 5%","SCORTEN should be calculated within 24 hours of admission AND repeated on day 3 — it accurately predicts mortality and guides level-of-care decisions","Nikolsky sign (lateral pressure causes epidermal separation) is positive in BOTH TEN and staphylococcal scalded skin syndrome (SSSS) — the key differentiator is histologic cleavage level on skin biopsy: TEN = full-thickness epidermal necrosis at the dermal-epidermal junction; SSSS = superficial intraepidermal split within the granular layer","Ocular complications are the most common long-term sequelae: symblepharon, dry eye syndrome, corneal scarring, and trichiasis can cause permanent vision loss — ophthalmology consultation within 24 hours is mandatory","HLA screening BEFORE prescribing high-risk drugs can prevent TEN: test HLA-B*5801 before allopurinol in Southeast Asian and African American patients; test HLA-B*1502 before carbamazepine in Southeast Asian patients","TEN patients lose massive amounts of fluid, protein, and heat through denuded skin — management parallels major burns but typically requires less aggressive fluid resuscitation","Systemic corticosteroids in TEN remain controversial: some studies suggest harm (increased infection risk, delayed healing), while others suggest possible benefit in early disease; cyclosporine has stronger emerging evidence"],
